New work sheet and calculated % of Total Hourly wages.

Click sheet 1 and open the new sheet. 


1.       Drag and drop Hire Date in the column shelves and   Hourly Wages in the row shelves.

         Click on Automatic drop down and select Bar Chart. 


Right Click on [Sum (Hourly wages)] then   Quick Table Calculation, then Percent of Total.

Now, drag and drop Region on the Color shelves and Hourly wages and Region on the Level. 


Right click on sheet name then click Edit Title. 


Title name % of Total Hourly Wages   and click ok. 



Click the Central Region and only Central Region showing the bottom picture. 





Using the bottom link:

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mprHDQzPLiI
